main event: An unidentified aluminum sheet was found on the ground in Grand Rapids, Michigan on March 1, 1961.
interesting points: The sighting was evaluated and concluded to be possibly a balloon or aircraft,No additional reports were received by the country regarding this sighting,The object was described as an aluminum alloy sheet measuring 34 inches by 13 feet,Local OSI dispatched an agent to the scene for investigation,The time of the incident was reported as 8:50 PM.
